<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="pt">
  <head>
    <title>Menus for PyG&ecirc;BR</title>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <!-- CSS only -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.0/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-9aIt2nRpC12Uk9gS9baDl411NQApFmC26EwAOH8WgZl5MYYxFfc+NcPb1dKGj7Sk" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <!-- Fontawesome Kit -->
    <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/ea00a9a22a.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>

    <style>
      h1,h2,h3,h4 {font-family: 'Montserrat', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol', 'Noto Color Emoji';}
      h1 {padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 2px;}
      li.list-group-item.head {background-color: #333333; color: #e2c84c;}
      li.list-group-item.head a {padding-right: 5px; color: #e2c84c;}
      .author a {color: #a0a0a0;}
      .link a {color: #a0a0a0;} 
      .title {font-style: normal;}
      .file {font-style: normal;}
      .description{font-style: italic;}
      .filter {padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px;}
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>

    <div class="d-flex flex-row align-items-baseline mb-3 mx-3">
      <div class="p-3"><a href="https://gitlab.com/Biloti/pygebr/-/wikis/home">
	  <img src="https://gitlab.com/Biloti/pygebr/-/raw/main/img/pygebr-logo.svg?inline=false"
	  height="40px"></a>
      </div>
      <div class="flex-column d-none d-sm-none d-md-block">
	<h1>PyG&ecirc;BR Menus</h1>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">

      <p>Below is the list of menus PyG&ecirc;BR found in the paths informed in
	your local setup. These menus can be used to compose new flows, upon
	<code>LoadFlow()</code> function. Use the name quoted in
	parenthesis to refer to the menu.</p>

      <p>Note that this list doesn't update automaticaly. After
	updating PyG&ecirc;BR or installing new menus in your personal
	folders, rebuild this list manually, by
	calling <code>Catalog()</code> function from PyGÃªBR.</p>

      <div class="row">
	<div class="col-md-8">
	  <h4 class="filter">Menus</h4>
	</div>
	<div class="col-md-4">
	  <input class="form-control" id="myFilter" type="text" placeholder="Search term">
	</div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="row">
	<div class="col-sm-12">
	  <div class="list-group" id="Menus">
#include "menulist.html"
	  </div>
	</div>
      </div>
      
    </div> <!-- container -->

    <footer class="footer mt-auto py-3">
      <div class="container">
	<span class="text-muted">Created at ##TODAY##</span>
      </div>
    </footer>
    <!-- JS, Popper.js, and jQuery -->
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"
	    integrity="sha256-/xUj+3OJU5yExlq6GSYGSHk7tPXikynS7ogEvDej/m4="
	    crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.6.1/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-fQybjgWLrvvRgtW6bFlB7jaZrFsaBXjsOMm/tB9LTS58ONXgqbR9W8oWht/amnpF" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript">
      $(document).ready(function(){
	  $("#myFilter").on("keyup", function() {
	      var value = $(this).val().toLowerCase();
	      $("#Menus li").filter(function() {
		  $(this).toggle($(this).text().toLowerCase().indexOf(value) > -1)
	      });
	  });
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html> 
